                            <comment id="17226833" author="ahussein" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2020 16:56:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We had deployed that change on our internal cluster to reduce the overhead of full reload of the conf.&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=weichiu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;weichiu&quot;&gt;weichiu&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Jim_Brennan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Jim_Brennan&quot;&gt;Jim_Brennan&lt;/a&gt;, can you please take a look at the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop/pull/2436&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PR-2436&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17226901" author="jojochuang" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2020 17:55:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Anything reported by Daryn must be good &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Makes sense to me. I&apos;ve seen a case similar to what you reported where KMS accumulated lots of uncanceled tokens, and then KMS and ZK were rendered unstable. (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-16876&quot; title=&quot;KMS delegation tokens are memory expensive&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-16876&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-16876&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17226913" author="daryn" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2020 18:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Accumulation of tokens in the KMS is often the result of something like oozie disabling token cancellation for jobs. &#160;I&apos;m not sure if my patch for the RM to ignore a client requesting tokens not be cancelled is in the community (there&apos;s a big dump of my internal patches coming though) but it had a huge impact on outstanding tokens and stability.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17227879" author="jojochuang" created="Sun, 8 Nov 2020 00:07:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IIRC Spark doesn&apos;t cancel job tokens either. We had a user hitting KMS OOM because Spark jobs are created faster than they are deleted. As a quick workaround we reduced token life time (hadoop.kms.authentication.delegation-token.max-lifetime.sec) from 7 days to 1 hour. I didn&apos;t have the chance to simulate and reproduce. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the property mapreduce.job.complete.cancel.delegation.tokens applies to MR jobs. But I don&apos;t recall an overall config that applies to all applications.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17230860" author="jojochuang" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2020 19:00:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
